Attention 7th-12th graders:

-You must submit your attendance to your homeroom teacher everyday between 8AM-10AM. This is different from elementary school.

-Zoom meetings are strongly encouraged when you are available. Please have appropriate behavior and language while on zooms. Let others in your family know your camera is on. Planners are helpful to write down scheduled zoom meetings and work due dates.

Remote instruction is essential and we highly encourage you to devote time to each of your enrolled classes and contact your teachers with any questions.

***Thank you Mrs. Reuss for your Google Meet Expectation example***

post_text: MCUSD 40 faculty and staff were scheduled for professional development and remote learning meetings today. Instead administration pushed it back a day because our small little town needed help. An email went out for faculty and staff to help (which was not mandatory) with the clean up after the horrible storm last night. The MCUCD 40 family were out in force today. Over 2 dozen faculty and staff showed up to help, including the administration. They helped out dozens of people picking up trees and limbs and hauling them away. #marissastrong #thatsmydistrict #proud #mcusd40

The IHSA has come out with its modified Sports season. Here is how it pertains to Meteor sports, high school sports.

Fall Sports: Aug. 10 to Oct. 24 - Boys and Girls Golf and Cross Country

Winter Sports: Nov. 16-Feb. 13 - Boys and Girls Basketball and Cheerleading

Spring Sports: Feb. 15-May 1 - Volleyball

Summer Sports: May 3-June 26 - Baseball and Softball

To read full IHSA plan click this link. https://www.ihsa.org/News-Media/Announcements/ihsa-board-announces-modified-schedule-for-2020-21-school-year

Again, this is for HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS. A decision will be made for junior high sports tomorrow.

Reminder athletes must have a sports physical before the first practice.

PLEASE NOTE: This is the IHSA plan. It still needs approved by the IDPH and the Governor's office.

post_text:
To: The Marissa District Family
From: Summer Food Service Program

Monday Greetings, Everyone!

On behalf of all of us working to provide meals for the students of Marissa District 40, we share our appreciation for your continued participation! Please note, with respect to the the Celebration of our Country's Independence Day, the school district and all offices will be Closed on Friday, July 3rd.

With that, we will be providing TWO DISTRIBUTIONS only this week- Today, Monday, June 29th, with meals for today and tomorrow, and Wednesday, July 1st, with meals for Wednesday, Thursday, and Friday.

Thank you very much for your participation and have a wonderful Independence Day Weekend!

Saint Louis University is excited to bring exceptional online courses provided by the 1818 Advanced College Credit Program to high school students across the United States through the inaugural Summer At SLU Academy.

Summer at SLU Academy courses begin on June 29, 2020, and end on Aug. 9, 2020. The deadline to enroll in courses is 11:59 p.m. (CST) June 22, 2020. https://www.slu.edu/summer/summer-at-slu-academy.php

Choose from the following courses:

CMM 1200: Public Speaking

HIST 1600: History of the U.S. to 1865

MATH 1510: Calculus I*

PHYS 1220: General Physics I*

PSY 1010: General Psychology

Eligible high school students must meet the following requirements:
Juniors and Seniors: Minimum of 3.0 on 4.0 scale, or with a 2.5-2.99 with parent permission.
Sophomores: Minimum of 3.0 on 4.0 scale and with parent permission.

SATURDAY, MAY 16 - TOGETHER FOR SENIORS
The IHSA was scheduled to crown its first state champions of the spring on May 16th, a celebration of achievement that would have repeated each Saturday through mid-June. The culmination of a high school season is extra special for our seniors, as they leave their leadership and legacy behind to their underclass teammates. Senior student-athletes are encouraged to post a picture of themselves on social media in their uniform, favorite school apparel, or the IHSA Student Advisory Committee‚Äôs Salute to Seniors shirts. We hope communities at large will post on social media in support of their seniors, recalling their favorite memories and the impact they have had during their four years.#WeAreInThisTogether #IHSA

FRIDAY, MAY 15 ‚Äì TOGETHER FOR EDUCATORS
Educators around the state have gone the extra mile in working with their students digitally over the past two months. On Friday night, when over 400 IHSA schools are expected to turn on the lights at their schools and athletic complexes for the ‚ÄúLights for the Fight‚Äù initiative, we are asking students and community members to brighten social media with their own thanks to all the teachers and coaches who have helped light their path. Lights For The Fight is about honoring first responders and essential workers, so we encourage recognition for those brave individuals, who like educators, are inspiring in their efforts to put others first.#WeAreInThisTogether #IHSA

THURSDAY, MAY 14 - TOGETHER FOR ATHLETES
America‚Äôs Original March Madness came to a sudden conclusion this year, as the 2020 IHSA Boys Basketball State Finals were unable to be played, and the IHSA‚Äôs spring sports eventually suffered the same fate. We encourage all high school teams, coaches, parents, fans, and athletes to post pictures and share memories from their high school sports experiences on Facebook, Twitter, and Instagram. In addition, the IHSA will recognize the eight schools (Aurora Christian, Goreville, Madison, Roanoke-Benson, Breese Mater Dei, Chicago Orr, Timothy Christian, and Sacred Heart-Griffin) who qualified for the 2020 COUNTRY Financial IHSA Boys Basketball Class 1A and Class 2A State Finals. #WeAreInThisTogether #IHSA

post_text:
Good Evening, Everyone.

I'd like to invite you to watch the YouTube video of today's press conference provided by the Governor. In the first 12 minutes of the 24 minute presser, Governor Pritzker spoke to all students, parents, teachers, food service workers, bus drivers, administrators, and support staff whose lives are impacted by the school closure extension and the difficulty in such a decision. Not only did he briefly recognize schools around the state, one being nearby Red Bud, but he also seemed to be speaking directly to us and our Marissa community in making mention to the many facets that make up our education process. Please, if you're seeing this message, I encourage you to view the message when you have about 12 minutes of free time. Yes, students- especially you Seniors- you are featured, and I hope you watch it. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YtgjqFYQ-k8

Sincerely,
Jeff Strieker, Superintendent

To: Marissa District 40 Family
Re: Next Learning Packet Delivery

Happy Thursday Greetings, Everyone!

I‚Äôd like to share a quick reminder that our teachers and staff have been putting together the next set of materials for our Remote Learning Packets, which will be delivered to you NEXT MONDAY, APRIL 20th, in the afternoon, with the buses rolling out of the Elementary at 1 PM. In addition, the packets that you‚Äôve been working on since last Wednesday can be turned in when you receive your new packet. Please do your best to meet the bus, so that we may help your mail carriers out by keeping your mailboxes empty. Any packets that are not able to be delivered will be taken back to the Elementary School. If you missed your packet and/or missed turning in work from the last packet, please call 295-2313, ext. 301 and leave me a message, so that arrangements can be made to make the connection. And again, thanks so much for your cooperation and participation!

Sincerely,

Jeff Strieker, Superintendent

post_text:
To: Marissa District 40 Family
Re: All-Call and Full Update tomorrow (Tuesday)

Good Evening/Good Morning, Marissa D. 40 Family!

I just wanted to share a quick heads-up prior to sharing an All Call tomorrow, pertaining to TWO THINGS:

1) Continual Remote Learning Packet #2: is being delivered on Wednesday afternoon, with the buses set to roll out of the Elementary at 1 PM. (Yes, PLEASE place the materials sent out in Packet #1 back in the folder/envelope in which it was delivered and hand it to the awesome delivery staff when they pass out #2)

2) Food Service Meals Distribution: After providing meals this week each day, the Distribution will change to Mondays, Wednesdays, and Fridays, beginning next Monday, April 13th.

Much more information coming in a full update tomorrow.
Thank you,

Jeff Strieker, Superintendent

...and a quick follow-up, if you don't mind.

Reports have been made on social media and local broadcast media that children/students around St. Clair County were NOT adhering to the guidelines of 'not congregating'- whether it be in parks, parking lots, houses, etc., PLEASE follow the guidelines. Our local parks are 'open to walking for exercise' but the playgrounds, basketball courts, etc. remain closed, especially for groups. Thank you so much for your understanding. JS
